<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_04.gif"><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/clear.gif" height=35 width=1></td>
<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Tournament Reports</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Tournament Reports</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/treports/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/treports/treports.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/treports/treports.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Artists in the Mountains Missoula May11<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(3.50)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=4454'>Cody "blackgecko" Custis</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=4454&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> May 11, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> A tournament report from the Rocky Mountains, where dwarves get bonuses.<br>
<br>
I recently downloaded a copy of Chrono Trigger, so I have been playing that like mad, and wish I would have done that long ago. Anyway, I wasnt sure if I would go to the tourney, since I hadnt talked to Big Country last night. I put on my Billings Mustangs shirt anyway, in order to gain the power of the Pioneer League champs. Around 11:45, BC walks in, and we drive to the Splash Page. Twelve people showed up, not bad considering how small a market Missoula is, and that the tourney scene here, excepting Magic, is really new. I buy a pack before, and pull Lurtz. Put him and a Hobbit Stealth into my Small, Fast, and Short deck, and also replaced the stupid Parol Troop with Flankers, which are infinitely more dangerous and useful. Lurtz doesnt get bonuses, but I have plenty of twilight around, and he just scares people. We had cool prizes, like the first person to win by corruption would get a set of twilight Nazgul, and the first person to win with the Balrog would get some toys, like the Whip and Sword. Jeremy, our TD, announces, and I get the bye. However, a new entry shows up, so I get to play.<br>
<br>
Game 1, Matt.<br>
I bid 1, and does he, but I win the roll and decide to go first. Hes running Uruk-Hai, but so am I. I complete my dash to site 3, as does he. Nothing too exciting happened, until I made my huge move, at site 6 or 7. I get the scimitar/scavenger/host deck, starting with a hand full of shadow. I have three guys on Frodo. However, he has the Coat, and the guys were wimps, so after he plays a card to make a Scrabbler minus three, I only get 11 power on Frodo, so he lives. I get to site 9, but only have three guys and Frodo, and he plays four Uruk-Hai, so Frodo got overwhelmed as time expired. Frodo is such a wimp. FL<br>
<br>
Game 2 Bill<br>
Same bid. He plays Sauron and Dwarves. I get the major swarm going, but he plays Here Lies Balin, Son of Fundin twice, turning a swarm of seven guys into a swarm of three. However, I kept the movement up, and he never caught up. On the last turn, even though tie was out and he couldnt win, I throw down the Lurtz. He kills Lurtz, which is nifty. FW<br>
<br>
Game 3 Mary<br>
She is playing dwarves and Uruk-Hai, I think. On site 3, turn 1, I get out 4 guys, and do bad man things. Next turn, I get our seven orcs, and overwhelm Frodo. A very short game. I get a prize for being the first person done, which is a random rare from the TD. I pull the guy who makes Gandalfs artifacts cheap, and trade him to Jermey for Golon, who helps my deck. FW<br>
<br>
Game 4 Jesse.<br>
He gets no fellowship the entire game. He started Aragorn, and sent Uruk-Hai. I do some damage on Aragron with a Backstabber at site 4, to set up the Balrog. At site five, common Balrog does his thing, and he loses Aragorn, but stealths Frodo alive. When I get to site 6, there is some controversy. He plays Lurtz and friend, I say archery, we both say pass, we get to maneuver, he says pass, I pass. I then point out that he forgot to make Lurtz fierce. He then goes Well if you want to play like that Hey, maybe it was a jerk thing to do, but he obviously knew what he was doing, and should have spotted for make Lurtz fierce. He then argued that I did the phases out of order, and I let him back up and make Lurtz fierce. I assign the wimp, who Fror takes, then assign Lurtz to Gimli, who I thought I could pump up to kill Lurtz. He pumps Lurtz more, so I lose Gimli, then have to lose the Farin, leaving lone Fror and Frodo on my side. However, on his turn, lone Frodo get whacked by three of my orcs, ending the game. I am the fastest winner again, and get the booby joke rare, The Weight of a Legacy. I guess I am happy, since Golon helps my deck. FW <br>
<br>
I took third, and won a No-Fi Soul Rebellion CD. That is good, since I have been meaning to buy them for some time. Afterward, Kris and Jeff play for fun.<br>
<br>
Bonus: Kris versus Jeff<br>
Frodo was in such a hurry to go, that we took a burden, and felt the call of evil. They both play dwarves, Jeffs straight up, Kris with friends. Kris is goblin swarm, Jeff is Sauron corruption and other tricks. Jeff sends raids of three guys, and gets Thin and Stretched / Desperate Defense of the Ring going early. Jeff plays the discard tale, so Kris loses from the draw deck constantly. Jeff gets all his dwarves pumped, and does bad man things with them. In the end, Jeffs deck is too much, as Kris runs out of cards and steam. <br>
<br>
Afterward, I give Jeff a quarter in exchange for my choice of the commons from the packs he got for winning to tourney. He gives me the Nazgul who resurrects guys for each companion over four, and the site 8 that adds archery for each guy over four. The next tourney in the area is May 25, with a 4$ entry, and states are in Bozeman on Jun 1st, which I probably wont go to. <br>
<br>
Props<br>
www.nofisoulrebellion.com The full band in attendance.<br>
www.shrimpers.org Billings style music. <br>
Jermey, for inventing nifty prizes, and giving story to the tourneys. Keep giving new and unique prizes. <br>
<br>
Slops<br>
Professors who assign papers with 2 weeks in the semester, without warning nor syllabus.<br>
Whoever decided that the SNES9.x would get super sensitive to a joystick that I cant calibrate right, making Chrono Trigger thrice as hard. I should go buy USB.<br>
Wally world, for not having my pictures on Wednesday.<br>
Rudys II, for not having Chris Sabo cards. <br>
